# Bloom position lock

Bloom placement is **intentionally frozen** and documented in `notes/BLOOM_TUNING.md`.

## Do not change when updating avatar / torch / GLB

- `BLOOM_TORCH_LOCK` in `player3d.js` (screen anchor K4, nudge 0/0)
- Screen-space bloom placement (`placeBloomAtScreen`, `screenAnchorToWorld`)
- Parenting bloom orbs to `scene` (not `flameAnchor` or torch nodes)

## OK to change with avatar/torch work

- `MODEL_URL`, skeletal animation, avatar framing, torch mesh materials
- `FLAME_LOCAL_OFFSET`, `POINT_LIGHT_SCREEN`, flame shader — these affect flame/lights, not bloom anchor

## If bloom must move

Edit `BLOOM_TORCH_LOCK` only on purpose, update `notes/BLOOM_TUNING.md`, and bump `?v=banker_new_*` cache bust.
